{"parse":{"title":"Institute for the Study of Totalitarian Regimes","pageid":27985663,"revid":833954567,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption class=\"fn org\">Institute for the Study of Totalitarian Regimes</caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Logo_USTR.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Logo USTR.png\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/78/Logo_USTR.png/220px-Logo_USTR.png\" width=\"220\" height=\"62\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/78/Logo_USTR.png/330px-Logo_USTR.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/78/Logo_USTR.png/440px-Logo_USTR.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1681\" data-file-height=\"473\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Formation</th><td class=\"note\">\n2007</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Type</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Government_agency\" title=\"Government agency\">Government agency</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Research_institute\" title=\"Research institute\">research institute</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Location</th><td class=\"label\">\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Prague\" title=\"Prague\">Prague</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Director</div></th><td>\n<a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Zden%C4%9Bk_Hazdra&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Zden\u011bk Hazdra (page does not exist)\">Zden\u011bk Hazdra</a><span class=\"noprint\" style=\"font-size:85%; font-style: normal;\">&#160;(<a href=\"https://cs.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zden%C4%9Bk_Hazdra\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"cs:Zden\u011bk Hazdra\">cs</a>)</span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Affiliations</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Platform_of_European_Memory_and_Conscience\" title=\"Platform of European Memory and Conscience\">Platform of European Memory and Conscience</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Website</th><td>\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ustrcr.cz\">ustrcr.cz</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>Institute for the Study of Totalitarian Regimes</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Czech_language\" title=\"Czech language\">Czech</a>: <i><span lang=\"cs\">\u00dastav pro studium totalitn\u00edch re\u017eim\u016f</span></i>) is a <a href=\"/wiki/Czech_Republic\" title=\"Czech Republic\">Czech</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Government_agency\" title=\"Government agency\">government agency</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Research_institute\" title=\"Research institute\">research institute</a>, founded by the Czech government in 2007.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Czech_Radio_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Czech_Radio-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\nIt is situated at Siwiecova street, Prague (the street is named after <a href=\"/wiki/Ryszard_Siwiec\" title=\"Ryszard Siwiec\">Ryszard Siwiec</a>).\n</p><p>Its purpose is to gather, analyse and make accessible documents from the <a href=\"/wiki/Nazi\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Nazi\">Nazi</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Communist\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Communist\">Communist</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Totalitarian\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Totalitarian\">totalitarian</a> regimes. The archives will also have documents from the former state <a href=\"/wiki/Secret_police\" title=\"Secret police\">secret police</a>, the <a href=\"/wiki/StB\" title=\"StB\">StB</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Czech_Radio_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Czech_Radio-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Bruce_I._Konviser_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Bruce_I._Konviser-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\nThe institute is a founding member organisation of the <a href=\"/wiki/Platform_of_European_Memory_and_Conscience\" title=\"Platform of European Memory and Conscience\">Platform of European Memory and Conscience</a>, and hosts its secretariat.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Platform_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Platform-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:%C3%9Astav_pro_studium_totalitn%C3%ADch_re%C5%BEim%C5%AF.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/35/%C3%9Astav_pro_studium_totalitn%C3%ADch_re%C5%BEim%C5%AF.jpg/220px-%C3%9Astav_pro_studium_totalitn%C3%ADch_re%C5%BEim%C5%AF.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"293\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/35/%C3%9Astav_pro_studium_totalitn%C3%ADch_re%C5%BEim%C5%AF.jpg/330px-%C3%9Astav_pro_studium_totalitn%C3%ADch_re%C5%BEim%C5%AF.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/35/%C3%9Astav_pro_studium_totalitn%C3%ADch_re%C5%BEim%C5%AF.jpg/440px-%C3%9Astav_pro_studium_totalitn%C3%ADch_re%C5%BEim%C5%AF.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3312\" data-file-height=\"4416\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:%C3%9Astav_pro_studium_totalitn%C3%ADch_re%C5%BEim%C5%AF.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Institute for the Study of Totalitarian Regimes, Prague, Siwiecova street</div></div></div>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Kundera_controversy\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Kundera controversy</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Raymond_Mawby\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Raymond Mawby</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Exhibition\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Exhibition</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Directors\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Directors</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Kundera_controversy\">Kundera controversy</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Institute_for_the_Study_of_Totalitarian_Regimes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Kundera controversy\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In 2008 the Institute for the Study of Totalitarian Regimes received media attention when a researcher published a controversial claim that the writer <a href=\"/wiki/Milan_Kundera\" title=\"Milan Kundera\">Milan Kundera</a> had been a <a href=\"/wiki/Police_informant\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Police informant\">police informant</a> who, in 1950, gave information leading to the arrest of a guest in a student hall of residence.  The arrested man, Miroslav Dvo\u0159\u00e1\u010dek, was sentenced to 22 years imprisonment as a spy. He served 14 years of his sentence, which included hard labour in a <a href=\"/wiki/Uranium_mine\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Uranium mine\">uranium mine</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Anne_Penketh_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Anne_Penketh-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Institute endorsed the authenticity of the 1950 police report on which the account was based, but indicated that it was not possible to establish some key facts. Kundera denied his involvement saying, \"I object in the strongest manner to these accusations, which are pure lies\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rachel_Donadio_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rachel_Donadio-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Raymond_Mawby\">Raymond Mawby</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Institute_for_the_Study_of_Totalitarian_Regimes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Raymond Mawby\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In 2012 the BBC reported that one of its researchers, who visited Prague in connection with a programme about a putative Czech attempt to compromise <a href=\"/wiki/Edward_Heath\" title=\"Edward Heath\">Edward Heath</a>, came across an extensive secret service file on Conservative MP <a href=\"/wiki/Raymond_Mawby\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Raymond Mawby\">Raymond Mawby</a>. There was evidence that Mawby sold information to the Czechs in the 1960s, although as Mawby was deceased it was not possible to hear \"his side\" of the story.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Mawby_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Mawby-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Exhibition\">Exhibition</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Institute_for_the_Study_of_Totalitarian_Regimes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Exhibition\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The institute shows exhibitions from other countries and has developed its own touring exhibitions. \"Prague Through the Lens of the Secret Police\" (which was first shown in 2009 at the Permanent Representation of the Czech Republic to the European Union in Brussels) was reviewed in the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Harvard_Gazette\" title=\"Harvard Gazette\">Harvard Gazette</a></i>: Mark Kramer, a fellow and director at the <a href=\"/wiki/Harvard_Project_on_Cold_War_Studies\" title=\"Harvard Project on Cold War Studies\">Harvard Project on Cold War Studies</a> commented on the extent to which the communist regime monitored ordinary people. \"The Czech secret police went to great lengths to keep track of people who were perfectly innocuous. These weren\u2019t terrorists. They weren\u2019t dangers to the state.\" <sup id=\"cite_ref-Corydon_Ireland_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Corydon_Ireland-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Directors\">Directors</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Institute_for_the_Study_of_Totalitarian_Regimes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Directors\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Pavel_%C5%BD%C3%A1%C4%8Dek\" title=\"Pavel \u017d\u00e1\u010dek\">Pavel \u017d\u00e1\u010dek</a> (2008\u20132010)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Ji%C5%99%C3%AD_Pernes\" title=\"Ji\u0159\u00ed Pernes\">Ji\u0159\u00ed Pernes</a> (2010)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Zden%C4%9Bk_Hazdra&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Zden\u011bk Hazdra (page does not exist)\">Zden\u011bk Hazdra</a> (2010, acting)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Daniel_Herman\" title=\"Daniel Herman\">Daniel Herman</a> (2010\u20132013)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Pavla_Foglov%C3%A1&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Pavla Foglov\u00e1 (page does not exist)\">Pavla Foglov\u00e1</a> (2013\u20132014)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Zden%C4%9Bk_Hazdra&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Zden\u011bk Hazdra (page does not exist)\">Zden\u011bk Hazdra</a> (2014\u2013 )<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Institute_for_the_Study_of_Totalitarian_Regimes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Post_Bellum\" title=\"Post Bellum\">Post Bellum</a> Czech NGO which created oral history project <a href=\"/wiki/Memory_of_Nation\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Memory of Nation\">Memory of Nation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Platform_of_European_Memory_and_Conscience\" title=\"Platform of European Memory and Conscience\">Platform of European Memory and Conscience</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Institute_for_the_Study_of_Totalitarian_Regimes&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Czech_Radio-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Czech_Radio_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Czech_Radio_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.radio.cz/ru/novosti/92239\">\"Daily News Summary\"</a>. <i>Czech Radio</i>. Cesky Rozhlas. 8 June 2007<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">9 July</span> 2010</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Czech+Radio&amp;rft.atitle=Daily+News+Summary&amp;rft.date=2007-06-08&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.radio.cz%2Fru%2Fnovosti%2F92239&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInstitute+for+the+Study+of+Totalitarian+Regimes\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Bruce_I._Konviser-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Bruce_I._Konviser_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Konviser, Bruce I. (16 August 2009). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.globalpost.com/dispatch/czech-republic/090805/the-institute-the-study-totalitarian-regimes\">\"Writing the history books\"</a>. Global Post<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">9 July</span> 2010</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Writing+the+history+books&amp;rft.date=2009-08-16&amp;rft.aulast=Konviser&amp;rft.aufirst=Bruce+I.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.globalpost.com%2Fdispatch%2Fczech-republic%2F090805%2Fthe-institute-the-study-totalitarian-regimes&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AInstitute+for+the+Study+of+Totalitarian+Regimes\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Platform-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Platform_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.memoryandconscience.eu/2011/10/20/czech-prime-minister-petr-necas-the-years-of-totalitarianism-were-years-of-struggle-for-liberty/\">\"Czech Prime minister Petr Ne\u010das: The years of totalitarianism w